<subSubSection id="68FB77B3B115B9230A503F9776E58B66" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="notes">
<paragraph id="48B9FEE2030BFDC145C9530FE30DFA2A" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A72FC2DDABD902496F8204EDD9EC216B" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName id="E53AB269B6E967E085A1082E061B0EB6" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ceratostomataceae" genus="Microthecium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Microthecium brevirostratum" order="Melanosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="brevirostratum">Microthecium brevirostratum</taxonomicName>
together with 
<taxonomicName id="9D797E384846FE8A820D66FE9914A9DD" genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. fayodii" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="fayodii">Mi. fayodii</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C03288B6C548976A3463FAC437E3337D" genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. pegleri" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="pegleri">Mi. pegleri</taxonomicName>
produces ostiolate ascomata, smooth-walled, ellipsoidal to navicular or citriform ascospores and bulbils. 
<taxonomicName id="FA6BB64286417F7CDCC11676BC8FB7BE" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ceratostomataceae" genus="Microthecium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Microthecium brevirostratum" order="Melanosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="brevirostratum">Microthecium brevirostratum</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished by ascospores with apiculate germ pores and the presence of a phialidic asexual morph (ascospores show depressed germ pores and lack an asexual morph in other species). 
<taxonomicName id="A3C3E38681686376796632B6ED6EA624" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ceratostomataceae" genus="Microthecium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Microthecium fayodii" order="Melanosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="fayodii">Microthecium fayodii</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="353952D8B28F91E3E6B1319D23EC22F6" genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. pegleri" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="pegleri">Mi. pegleri</taxonomicName>
differ in the size of the ascospores, 
<taxonomicName id="09A45C6533BB594F4B5BEBD54ECB633A" genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. pegleri" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="pegleri">Mi. pegleri</taxonomicName>
having the smallest ascospores in 
<taxonomicName id="A6E4383435BFC988EFE3BE0E5ED53A44" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ceratostomataceae" genus="Microthecium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Microthecium" order="Melanosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Microthecium</taxonomicName>
[(9.5
<normalizedToken id="B7B4F611770A6BDE8711763840FB96C0" originalValue="–)11–12(–">-)11-12(-</normalizedToken>
13) 
<normalizedToken id="D0BC008ECF4480A9D3CA213FF4BC2B8A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4-4.5 
